SUMMARY:Volunteer Income Tax Assistance (VITA) Program Session
DESCRIPTION:The Indiana University IRS VITA program offers free tax prepa
 ration services for qualifying low-income taxpayers during the spring sem
 ester.  VITA services will be available at Maurer School of Law on Monday
  and Tuesday evenings from 6:30 to 9:30 p.m. in Room 121 of the Law Schoo
 l (211 South Indiana Avenue) on a first-come\, first-served basis.  For m
 ore information on whether you qualify and what you should bring\, see Ma
 urer's VITA or United Way's websites. Or contact Maurer VITA student liai
 son Ben Batchelder at benbatch@iu.edu (mailto:benbatch@iu.edu).&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The Indiana University IRS VITA program
  offers free tax preparation services for qualifying low-income taxpayers
  during the spring semester.</p><p>  VITA services will be available at M
 aurer School of Law on Monday and Tuesday evenings from 6:30 to 9:30 p.m.
  in Room 121 of the Law School (211 South Indiana Avenue) on a first-come
 \, first-served basis.</p><p>  For more information on whether you qualif
 y and what you should bring\, see Maurer's VITA or United Way's websites.
  Or contact Maurer VITA student liaison Ben Batchelder at <a href="mailto
 :benbatch@iu.edu">benbatch@iu.edu</a>.&#160\;</p>
